Let the given determinant be
\begin{align*} \begin{vmatrix} 1 & \cos (a - b) & \cos a \\ \cos(a - b) & 1 & \cos b \\ \cos a & \cos b & 1 \end{vmatrix} &= \begin{vmatrix} 1 & \cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b & \cos a \\ \cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b & 1 & \cos b \\ \cos a & \cos b & 1 \end{vmatrix} \\ &= 1 \begin{vmatrix} 1 & \cos b \\ \cos b & 1 \end{vmatrix} - (\cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b) \begin{vmatrix} \cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b & \cos b \\ \cos a & 1 \end{vmatrix} \\ &\quad + \cos a \begin{vmatrix} \cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b & 1 \\ \cos a & \cos b \end{vmatrix} \\ &= 1(1 - \cos^2 b) - (\cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b) (\cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b - \cos a \cos b) \\ &\quad + \cos a ((\cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b) \cos b - \cos a) \\ &= 1 - \cos^2 b - (\cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b) (\sin a \sin b) + \cos a (\cos a \cos^2 b + \sin a \sin b \cos b - \cos a) \\ &= 1 - \cos^2 b - \cos a \cos b \sin a \sin b - \sin^2 a \sin^2 b + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b + \cos a \sin a \sin b \cos b - \cos^2 a \\ &= 1 - \cos^2 b - \cos^2 a - \sin^2 a \sin^2 b + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b \\ &= 1 - \cos^2 b - \cos^2 a - \sin^2 a \sin^2 b + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b \\ &= (1 - \cos^2 a) - \cos^2 b + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b - \sin^2 a \sin^2 b \\ &= \sin^2 a - \cos^2 b + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b - \sin^2 a \sin^2 b \\ &= \sin^2 a (1 - \sin^2 b) - \cos^2 b (1 - \cos^2 a) \\ &= \sin^2 a \cos^2 b - \cos^2 b \sin^2 a \\ &= 0. \end{align*}

We have
\begin{align*} \begin{vmatrix} 1 & \cos (a - b) & \cos a \\ \cos(a - b) & 1 & \cos b \\ \cos a & \cos b & 1 \end{vmatrix} &= 1(1 - \cos^2 b) - \cos(a - b) (\cos(a - b) - \cos a \cos b) + \cos a (\cos(a - b) \cos b - \cos a) \\ &= \sin^2 b - \cos(a - b) (\cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b - \cos a \cos b) + \cos a ((\cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b) \cos b - \cos a) \\ &= \sin^2 b - \cos(a - b) \sin a \sin b + \cos a (\cos a \cos^2 b + \sin a \sin b \cos b - \cos a) \\ &= \sin^2 b - (\cos a \cos b + \sin a \sin b) \sin a \sin b + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b + \cos a \sin a \sin b \cos b - \cos^2 a \\ &= \sin^2 b - \cos a \sin a \cos b \sin b - \sin^2 a \sin^2 b + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b + \cos a \sin a \sin b \cos b - \cos^2 a \\ &= \sin^2 b - \sin^2 a \sin^2 b + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b - \cos^2 a \\ &= \sin^2 b (1 - \sin^2 a) + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b - \cos^2 a \\ &= \sin^2 b \cos^2 a + \cos^2 a \cos^2 b - \cos^2 a \\ &= \cos^2 a (\sin^2 b + \cos^2 b) - \cos^2 a \\ &= \cos^2 a - \cos^2 a = 0. \end{align*}

Final Answer: The final answer is $\boxed{0}$

